Download the Mr Ping&#39;s noodle shop image and put it in your images directory.
Fixing the Image
Our image is far too big, so our advert takes up most of the page.  As we have given the image in the advert an id tag, we can define styles and image size in our css/styles.css file.

Note Edit the css/styles.css file and add the following styles to make our image a suitable size for our advert

Lets set the height and width of the noodle shop image to 64px, that is four times as big as the default size of the text.  We will also ad a margin to the right of the image to keep a nice gap between the image and the text.
#mr-pings-noodle-shop-img{
    height:64px;
    width:64px;
    margin-right:15px;
}

make-page-responsive/qualifications-sect.body:
Qualification Section
Now we include a section on Poh&#39;s qualifications.
Poh fell in love with Salesforce when he saw Trailhead and has now been busy completing the trails.

Note Lets add a new section for Qualifications

We create a row for our qualifications and in this row we have three columns, each defined by the ``
&lt;div class=&quot;col-md-12&quot;&gt; &lt;!-- Qualifications section --&gt;
     &lt;h2&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;

     &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;

       &lt;div class=&quot;col-sm-4&quot;&gt;&lt;!-- SLDS --&gt;
         &lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;images/trailhead_module_lightning_design_system.png&quot;
                 alt=&quot;Trailhead Module Lightning Design System&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
       &lt;/div&gt;

       &lt;div class=&quot;col-sm-4&quot;&gt;&lt;!-- Salesforce Lightning Experience --&gt;
         &lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;images/trailhead_module_lightning_design_system.png&quot;
                 alt=&quot;Trailhead Module Lightning Design System&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
       &lt;/div&gt;

       &lt;div class=&quot;col-sm-4&quot;&gt;&lt;!-- Salesforce Process Automation --&gt;
         &lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;images/trailhead_module_lightning_process_automation.png&quot;
                 alt=&quot;Trailhead Module Lightning Process Automation&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
       &lt;/div&gt;

     &lt;/div&gt;
   &lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- Qualifications section --&gt;

You should now see a row of Trailhead badges along the width of the web page

If you minimise the page to a table in portrait mode then you see a slight change to the spacing around the qualification images.

If you minimise the browser to be the size of a smart phone, you see that the qualification images are lined up on top of each other.

