Note Create a style for the images to make them all the same size.

Using the friends class with the img tag we can change the styles of just those images in the friends gallery, without affecting other images on the page
img.friends{
    width:128px;
    height:128px;
}

Now all our images in the gallery are the same size and this makes our web page look more professional and display correctly when viewed on different style devices.

Hint To make the gallery more interactive, I should add links to each of the images to take them to the friends profile or website.

Transparent backgrounds with images
As we have a coloured background on our website we should really use images with transparent backgrounds.  You can see some of the images already have transparent backgrounds, so you can see the pale blue colour through the images.
With transparent images, you do not need to worry about matching the image background colour with the webpage background colour.  So if you change the web page background, you should not need to change all the images.

